Orat. 26, 89 quaesita nec ex tempore ficta sed domo allata. —novam et recentem: The usual distinction between novus ‘ something that did not exist previously' and recens ‘what has not existed for a long time,' cannot be strictly maintained. Cf. Iuv. II 102 novis annalibus atque recenti historia, Tac. H. V. 13 apud veteres aut novis ingeniis and some of the passages cited by Schmidt, Handb. d. Synonymik p. 486 ff.
